gmp 4.1.2 install how-to:

Downloading and unpacking:
  ftp://ftp.cs.unipr.it/pub/infrastructure/gmp-4.1.2.tar.bz2
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  tar jxvf gmp-4.1.2.tar.bz2

Configuring and building (and optionally check the build):
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  mkdir obj-gmp
  cd obj-gmp
  ../gmp-4.1.2/configure --prefix=/usr/local --enable-cxx
  make
  make check

NOTE: if you want to build with support for exception handling
      (not required now) change the above configure command with:
CPPFLAGS=-fexceptions ../gmp-4.1.2/configure --prefix=/usr/local --enable-cxx

Installing (as root):
  su
  <give your root password>
  make install
  exit

============================================================================

cln-1.1.5 install how-to:

Downloading and unpacking:
  ftp://ftp.cs.unipr.it/pub/infrastructure/cln-1.1.5.tar.bz2
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  tar jxvf cln-1.1.5.tar.bz2

Configuring and building (and optionally check the build):
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  mkdir obj-cln
  cd obj-cln
  ../cln-1.1.5/configure --prefix=/usr/local
  make
  make check

Installing (as root):
  su
  <give your root password>
  make install
  exit

Note that the `make install' command will result in the following error
message, which you should simply *ignore*:

  /usr/bin/install: cannot stat `cln.m4': No such file or directory
  make: *** [install] Error 1

However, if you had already installed cln before (from inside
the source tree), then you should remove the previously installed
configuration file:
  su
  <give your root password>
  rm /usr/local/share/aclocal/cln.m4
  exit

============================================================================

ntl-5.3 install how-to:

Downloading and unpacking:
  ftp://ftp.cs.unipr.it/pub/infrastructure/ntl-5.3.tar.bz2
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  tar jxvf ntl-5.3.tar.bz2

Configuring and building (and optionally check the build):
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  cd ntl-5.3/src
  ./configure NTL_GMP_LIP=on NTL_STD_CXX=on GMP_PREFIX=/usr/local
  make
  make check

Installing (as root):
  su
  <give your root password>
  make install
  exit

============================================================================

GiNaC install how-to:

Downloading and unpacking:
  ftp://ftp.cs.unipr.it/pub/infrastructure/GiNaC-1.0.13-parma.tar.bz2
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  tar jxvf GiNaC-1.0.13-parma.tar.bz2

Configuring and building:
  cd your-path-to-download-dir
  mkdir obj-GiNaC
  cd obj-GiNaC
  ../GiNaC-1.0.13/configure --prefix=/usr/local
  make

Installing (as root):
  su
  <give your root password>
  make install
  exit

Checking whether you built right executable:
  ginsh
You should obtain the following output:

  ginsh - GiNaC Interactive Shell (GiNaC V1.0.13)
    __,  _______  Copyright (C) 1999-2003 Johannes Gutenberg University Mainz,
   (__) *       | Germany.  This is free software with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.
    ._) i N a C | You are welcome to redistribute it under certain conditions.
  <-------------' For details type `warranty;'.
  
  Type ?? for a list of help topics.
  > 
  <Type CTRL-D to exit the GiNaC shell>

